My friend chose this place to have a birthday get together. When we arrived it was completely empty (apparently they lost their customers to poor service). Regardless, we got comfortable ordered lots of food (which was pretty tasty, hence the 1 star) and drinks. When it came to eating the birthday cake, they refused to give us plates and forked because we wouldn't pay an extra $25 for the "cake cutting package". Mind you, the cake was already cut and all we needed for a few small saucers. This was extremely poor service considering we were their only business and we were spending money. Not going back. Will opt for other spots in the area (there's plenty).
